Appendix

Do not change, edit, or remove the R chunk included below.

If you are working within RStudio and within your Project1 RStudio project (check the top right-hand corner says “Project1”), then the code from the meme.R script will be displayed below.

This code needs to be visible for your project to be marked appropriately, as some of the criteria are based on this code being submitted.

library(magick)

meme_image <- image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/4fdpc1.png") %>%
  image_resize("800x450") #resize and read image being used

meme <- meme_image %>%
  image_annotate(
    text = "How it feels to leave the movie theatre mid day", #add text to meme
    color = "#ffffff", #color white
    size = 30, #smaller size to fit image
    font = "Impact", #impact font
    gravity = "north" #put text at top of image
    )
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png") #save the image as a png

frame1 <- meme_image %>% #creating first frame
  image_annotate(
    text = "How it feels to leave the movie theatre mid day", #text 
    color = "#ffffff", #color white
    size = 30, #smaller size to fit image
    font = "Impact", #impact font
    gravity = "north" #put text at top of image
  )

frame2_image <- image_charcoal(meme_image) #put an effect on the image
frame2 <- frame2_image %>%
  image_annotate(
    text = "How it feels to leave the movie theatre mid day", #text
    color = "#000000", #color black
    size = 30, #smaller size to fit image
    font = "Impact", #impact font
    gravity = "north" #put text at top of image
  )

frame3_image <- image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/28rgrp.jpg") %>%
  image_resize("800x450") #new image on frame 3 and resizing it
frame3 <- frame3_image %>%
  image_annotate(
    text = "How it feels to leave the movie theatre mid day", #text
    color = "#ffffff", #color white
    size = 30, #smaller size to fit image
    font = "Impact", #impact font
    gravity = "north" #put text at top of image
  )

frame4_image <- image_negate(frame3_image) #filter frame 3's image for 4
frame4 <- frame4_image %>%
  image_annotate(
    text = "How it feels to leave the movie theatre mid day", #text
    color = "#000000", #color black
    size = 30, #smaller size to fit image
    font = "Impact", #impact font
    gravity = "north" #put text at top of image
  )

frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4) #create vector with all 4 frames
animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1) #animating by using the vectors
image_write(animation, "my_animated_meme.gif") #save animation as gif
